The paper deals with image denoising, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. The proposed method is inspired by human vision, which suggests a connection to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method involves clustering and hierarchical structures, which are common in machine learning and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also evaluates the proposed method on two public datasets, which suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper proposes an extension of bilateral filtering, which is a classical image processing technique, suggesting a connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG).
